We only need to look at the rows that internally represent the paid‐in capital. In our transactions the “Initial20231231001” transactions are the opening cash injections. There are three such records:

• Cash deposit of 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit of 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets of 5,000,000.0  

Summing these gives 3,000,000 + 5,000,000 + 5,000,000 = 13,000,000.

Since no subsequent transaction modifies the paid‐in capital (only operating transactions occur), the opening (initial) paid‐in capital equals the ending paid‐in capital.

Thus, the answer is:
{"solution": {"Paid-in Capital Initial Value": "13000000.00", "Paid-in Capital End Value": "13000000.00"}}
